[{"id":"VR803400","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two conducting spheres are initially isolated. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> has radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 1\"><math alttext=\"r sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> and is initially uncharged. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 2\"><math alttext=\"r sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, such that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 1 is greater than r sub 2\"><math alttext=\"r sub 1 is greater than r sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, and has a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"positive uppercase Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. The two spheres are then connected by a conducting wire and allowed to reach equilibrium, resulting in a charge on Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly represents the charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase q\"><math alttext=\"lowercase q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> on Sphere <s